255
00:21:53,657 --> 00:21:55,624
- Who are you?
- I am a man.

256
00:21:55,977 --> 00:21:57,366
I can see that. Who are you?

257
00:21:57,446 --> 00:22:01,034
No matter how you
see it, I am the same.

258
00:22:01,324 --> 00:22:03,054
- What are you doing here?
- Working.

259
00:22:03,479 --> 00:22:05,328
- Working!
- Service, service.

260
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:07,240
I can understand Hindi.
What is your name?

261
00:22:07,641 --> 00:22:09,374
What can a poor man's name be, sir?

262
00:22:10,368 --> 00:22:12,713
- Call me whatever you want to.
- Would you tell me something?

263
00:22:12,737 --> 00:22:15,729
What do I tell you?
My parents have named me Madhav.

264
00:22:16,368 --> 00:22:18,487
But nobody calls a
poor man with his name.

265
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:19,966
Hey, you! Come here!

266
00:22:20,417 --> 00:22:22,248
Somebody calls me fool or idiot!

267
00:22:22,337 --> 00:22:24,407
- How did you come here?
- From the street.

268
00:22:24,487 --> 00:22:25,691
- The street?
- Yes. -Yes.

269
00:22:26,257 --> 00:22:28,248
Poor man was lying
on the street and..

270
00:22:28,337 --> 00:22:29,873
Getting drenched in
the rain since many days.

271
00:22:29,897 --> 00:22:32,047
I took pity on him. Ramu has left.

272
00:22:32,127 --> 00:22:33,411
So I kept him as our servant.

273
00:22:33,491 --> 00:22:35,886
Mother, you don't know a
person and you feel pity for him.

274
00:22:36,417 --> 00:22:38,487
You appoint a man lying on
the street, your servant.

275
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:39,646
- Son.
- Yes.

276
00:22:39,726 --> 00:22:42,033
You don't appoint those living
in bungalow as your servant.

277
00:22:42,057 --> 00:22:43,570
You find them on the street only.

278
00:22:44,497 --> 00:22:46,249
What is there to know?

279
00:22:47,055 --> 00:22:49,969
I saw him shelter less.
And I gave him shelter.

280
00:22:50,497 --> 00:22:51,566
Good.

281
00:22:57,977 --> 00:23:00,650
- The weather is so lovely.
- Very.

282
00:23:02,257 --> 00:23:04,896
- It is so cold.
- Yes.

283
00:23:06,457 --> 00:23:10,132
- I am still not engaged.
- Yes.

284
00:23:11,116 --> 00:23:12,968
I said I am still not engaged.

285
00:23:15,057 --> 00:23:16,968
- It won't happen too.
- Why?

286
00:23:17,817 --> 00:23:19,177
Because we will first get married.

287
00:23:19,211 --> 00:23:20,406
No need for engagement.

288
00:23:20,817 --> 00:23:23,577
You always jest. Do
be serious sometimes.

289
00:23:23,657 --> 00:23:27,657
Look, Seema. My position
at home is already serious.

290
00:23:27,737 --> 00:23:29,977
If I also got serious, then
everything will be in a mess.

291
00:23:30,673 --> 00:23:31,806
What do you mean?

292
00:23:32,257 --> 00:23:33,576
Mother has given me the notice.

293
00:23:34,137 --> 00:23:36,367
- What notice?
- To get married.

294
00:23:37,417 --> 00:23:39,137
Mother is fixing my
alliance somewhere else.

295
00:23:40,337 --> 00:23:42,487
What did you tell your mother?

296
00:23:43,817 --> 00:23:46,251
Seema, before mother
selects some other girl..

297
00:23:46,337 --> 00:23:49,727
It is very important
for you to meet mother.

298
00:23:53,054 --> 00:23:54,126
- Anand.
- Yes.

299
00:23:54,657 --> 00:23:56,727
What if mother didn't like me?

300
00:23:57,497 --> 00:23:59,328
If mother didn't like you..

301
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:01,966
Very simple!

302
00:24:02,057 --> 00:24:04,366
I will marry the
girl of mother's choice.

303
00:24:05,257 --> 00:24:07,054
Then go! What are you doing here?

304
00:24:08,497 --> 00:24:10,055
Romancing you.

305
00:24:11,057 --> 00:24:13,412
You love me and you
will marry somebody else.

306
00:24:13,817 --> 00:24:14,966
What is the harm?

307
00:24:17,457 --> 00:24:18,526
Why are you getting angry?

308
00:24:18,617 --> 00:24:21,734
I'll marry you and
love somebody else. Happy?

309
00:24:22,737 --> 00:24:26,571
Fine, I'll marry and
love only you. Happy?

310
00:24:28,059 --> 00:24:29,410
- Very happy!
- Very good!

311
00:24:29,497 --> 00:24:30,566
Leave my hand.

312
00:24:31,499 --> 00:24:37,049
"Leaving the support of your love."

313
00:24:37,137 --> 00:24:42,495
"Leaving the support of your love."

314
00:24:42,737 --> 00:24:47,731
"Tell me. Where will I go?"

315
00:24:48,417 --> 00:24:53,730
"I am afraid that in your arms."

316
00:24:54,057 --> 00:24:59,654
"I am afraid that in your arms."

317
00:24:59,737 --> 00:25:04,731
"Today I might die of happiness."

318
00:25:20,257 --> 00:25:25,377
"The distances of the
heart have today bridged."

319
00:25:25,897 --> 00:25:30,846
"I am standing near my destination."

320
00:25:31,337 --> 00:25:36,809
"When you smiled and glanced at me."

321
00:25:36,897 --> 00:25:41,732
"All the grievances of
the heart disappeared."

322
00:25:42,417 --> 00:25:47,730
"These precious
moments are so lovely."

323
00:25:48,057 --> 00:25:52,972
"Tell it to stop here only."

324
00:25:53,577 --> 00:25:58,970
"I am afraid that in your arms."

325
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:04,256
"Today I might die of happiness."

326
00:26:21,497 --> 00:26:26,571
"I will offer my life to your feet."

327
00:26:27,057 --> 00:26:31,972
"And the light of my eyes."

328
00:26:32,657 --> 00:26:34,727
"If you are happy."

329
00:26:34,817 --> 00:26:42,817
"Then I will bestow all the
happiness of my heart on yours."

330
00:26:43,657 --> 00:26:49,015
"My beloved, my happiness lies in."

331
00:26:49,257 --> 00:26:54,331
"Seeing you wherever I go."

332
00:26:54,817 --> 00:27:00,050
"Leaving the support of your love."

333
00:27:00,337 --> 00:27:05,331
"Tell me. Where will I go?"

334
00:27:20,817 --> 00:27:25,652
"Seeing love in these eyes."

335
00:27:26,337 --> 00:27:31,331
"Has lit the path with lamps."

336
00:27:31,897 --> 00:27:34,457
"If I had not met you."

337
00:27:34,537 --> 00:27:42,330
"Then this world would
have been a lonely place."

338
00:27:42,817 --> 00:27:48,335
"Tell your sighs."

339
00:27:48,417 --> 00:27:53,332
"Not to ever come on your lips."

340
00:27:53,817 --> 00:27:59,335
"Leaving the support of your love."

341
00:27:59,417 --> 00:28:04,332
"Tell me. Where will I go?"

342
00:28:04,737 --> 00:28:10,334
"I am afraid that in your arms."

343
00:28:10,417 --> 00:28:15,491
"Today I might die of happiness."

344
00:29:11,915 --> 00:29:13,046
Seema?

345
00:29:13,457 --> 00:29:14,526
Seema?

346
00:29:14,617 --> 00:29:15,686
Seema, what happened?

347
00:29:16,057 --> 00:29:17,126
What happened to you?

348
00:29:17,577 --> 00:29:18,646
What happened, Seema?

349
00:29:22,897 --> 00:29:23,966
What happened?

350
00:29:24,057 --> 00:29:27,434
- Injection.
- What? Who?

351
00:29:27,733 --> 00:29:29,329
Tell me.

352
00:29:33,935 --> 00:29:35,126
Seema!

353
00:29:40,777 --> 00:29:42,335
Cyanide's injection.

354
00:29:43,817 --> 00:29:45,017
Sit down, inspector. Sit down.

355
00:29:46,737 --> 00:29:52,369
SP.. I think only
doctors have this poison.

356
00:29:54,577 --> 00:30:00,129
Doctors, nurses, chemist,
hospitals, laboratories. No!

357
00:30:00,937 --> 00:30:02,655
No, inspector. You are mistaken.

358
00:30:03,057 --> 00:30:05,048
The oldest rule is the best rule.

359
00:30:06,941 --> 00:30:09,332
You find the motive and
you find the murderer.

360
00:30:10,257 --> 00:30:16,048
First try to find out who will
benefit from Seema's murder.

361
00:30:17,657 --> 00:30:20,257
And appoint two of
your special men..

362
00:30:20,337 --> 00:30:23,966
To keep a tight tab on
Dr. Lata and Dr. Singh.

363
00:30:24,617 --> 00:30:27,495
- Dr. Singh?
- Yes.

364
00:30:30,537 --> 00:30:31,811
Dr. Singh.

365
00:30:56,337 --> 00:30:58,337
Madhav! Hey, Madhav!

366
00:30:58,417 --> 00:30:59,486
Yes, sir.

367
00:31:01,257 --> 00:31:03,033
- What are you doing here?
- Nothing. I was sleeping.

368
00:31:03,057 --> 00:31:05,651
You didn't return soon.
But I fell asleep quickly.

369
00:31:05,731 --> 00:31:06,886
You have progressed a lot.

370
00:31:06,977 --> 00:31:08,257
From the street to the compound.

371
00:31:08,331 --> 00:31:09,462
From the compound to the hall.

372
00:31:09,486 --> 00:31:10,633
From here now go to my bedroom.

373
00:31:10,657 --> 00:31:11,726
As you say, sir.

374
00:31:11,817 --> 00:31:13,489
- Hey!
- Yes. Where are you going?

375
00:31:13,577 --> 00:31:15,457
You told me to sleep in
the bedroom, didn't you?

376
00:31:15,658 --> 00:31:17,966
- I told you to go to hell! Go!
- As you say, sir.

377
00:31:18,057 --> 00:31:19,331
Why are you getting angry?

378
00:31:19,897 --> 00:31:23,526
He just got up.
He is not fully awake.

379
00:31:23,848 --> 00:31:25,963
You are saying something and
he is hearing something else.

380
00:31:25,987 --> 00:31:27,799
- Madhav! Warm the food.
- Yes.

381
00:31:27,879 --> 00:31:30,491
- I won't eat, Mother.
- Why?

382
00:31:31,546 --> 00:31:32,906
I don't feel like eating anything.

383
00:31:34,497 --> 00:31:37,330
I know, son. I am your mother.

384
00:31:38,057 --> 00:31:40,048
I can understand your pain better.

385
00:31:41,057 --> 00:31:43,491
But you don't die with the deceased.

386
00:31:44,577 --> 00:31:48,331
Will Seema's soul find
peace seeing you in this state?

387
00:31:49,187 --> 00:31:50,849
She is dead.

388
00:31:51,659 --> 00:31:54,330
Had it been an extinguished lamp,
I'd have lit it again.

389
00:31:55,257 --> 00:31:57,248
Now the only thing I
can do is to bring..

390
00:31:57,337 --> 00:31:59,976
Another girl to
take Seema's place.

391
00:32:01,057 --> 00:32:02,968
It will alleviate your pain.

392
00:32:03,897 --> 00:32:05,313
Daughter-in-law will
come in this house.

393
00:32:05,337 --> 00:32:08,561
The isolation of this house, the
grief of your heart, my worries..

394
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:10,929
Everything will vanish.

395
00:32:11,657 --> 00:32:13,700
Tell me, Anand. Answer me!

396
00:32:13,977 --> 00:32:16,411
Say yes, son. Son, say yes.

397
00:32:29,958 --> 00:32:31,058
Hello?

398
00:32:31,147 --> 00:32:32,216
Dr. Anand speaking.

399
00:32:32,707 --> 00:32:34,026
Yes, Dr. Anand speaking.

400
00:32:34,627 --> 00:32:37,061
Sorry, doctor. You don't know me.

401
00:32:37,490 --> 00:32:40,778
But a patient at our
home is very sick.

402
00:32:41,547 --> 00:32:42,627
From where are you calling?

403
00:32:43,303 --> 00:32:44,983
I am calling from the
public phone, doctor.

404
00:32:45,627 --> 00:32:47,219
I don't know your
residential address.

405
00:32:47,882 --> 00:32:50,785
I'll be waiting for you at
the post office circle, doctor.

406
00:32:51,627 --> 00:32:53,140
Doctor, do come. Please, doctor.

407
00:32:53,467 --> 00:32:55,267
Somebody's life and
death is at stake, doctor.

408
00:32:55,702 --> 00:32:56,902
Please! Please, doctor!

409
00:32:57,818 --> 00:33:00,546
Post office circle.
Fine, I'll be right over.

410
00:33:01,568 --> 00:33:03,982
Thank you. Thanks a lot, doctor.

411
00:33:13,707 --> 00:33:14,707
Are you Dr. Anand?

412
00:33:14,734 --> 00:33:16,585
Did you call me to
visit the patient?

413
00:33:16,667 --> 00:33:17,947
- Yes, I had called.
- Come, sit.

414
00:33:18,027 --> 00:33:19,096
Hurry up, doctor.

415
00:33:20,867 --> 00:33:23,506
- Where do we have to go?
- I will direct you the way.

416
00:33:55,467 --> 00:33:56,536
Come, doctor.

417
00:34:13,867 --> 00:34:15,016
Come, doctor.

418
00:34:21,547 --> 00:34:23,503
Extend your hand
towards the right side.

419
00:34:24,387 --> 00:34:26,617
The candle is kept there. Light it.

420
00:34:41,627 --> 00:34:43,857
Come. Come upstairs.

421
00:34:48,547 --> 00:34:49,616
Come.

422
00:35:08,307 --> 00:35:13,859
Such a huge house. And a
sick person. And no light!

423
00:35:14,627 --> 00:35:15,776
What do I tell you, doctor?

424
00:35:16,467 --> 00:35:22,303
I am a poor man.
The radiance of the house is long gone.

425
00:35:44,846 --> 00:35:47,780
Go away! Why have you come now!

426
00:35:48,827 --> 00:35:52,740
My daughter is dead!
She is dead! She is dead!

427
00:36:07,627 --> 00:36:11,779
My daughter is dead!
She is dead! You go away!

428
00:36:17,907 --> 00:36:22,219
Take this doctor away!
He's a butcher! He's stone hearted.

429
00:36:22,307 --> 00:36:24,616
- Doctor! Come with me.
- Take him away!

430
00:36:24,707 --> 00:36:30,464
Take him away! Take him away!
I say take him away!

431
00:36:52,427 --> 00:36:57,899
Doctor, I am sorry.

432
00:37:30,947 --> 00:37:32,016
Who are you?

433
00:37:32,947 --> 00:37:35,017
I am a doctor. Dr. Anand.

434
00:37:35,707 --> 00:37:36,776
Why did you come here?

435
00:37:39,787 --> 00:37:40,936
To see a patient.

436
00:37:42,627 --> 00:37:45,095
- You entered this bungalow?
- Yes.

437
00:37:50,387 --> 00:37:51,867
What's the matter, Inspector?

438
00:37:54,227 --> 00:37:56,457
Did somebody call
you to see the patient?

439
00:37:57,787 --> 00:37:58,856
Yes.

440
00:37:59,307 --> 00:38:00,899
And that patient
was a beautiful girl.

441
00:38:02,307 --> 00:38:03,376
Yes.

442
00:38:03,787 --> 00:38:05,618
And she died before you came here.

443
00:38:08,627 --> 00:38:09,696
Yes.

444
00:38:10,307 --> 00:38:12,298
And an old lady sitting
besides her was crying.

445
00:38:13,227 --> 00:38:15,695
All this is true, inspector.
But how do you know it?

446
00:38:17,107 --> 00:38:21,305
Doctor, I very well know that
this bungalow is vacant since ages.

447
00:38:24,027 --> 00:38:27,099
Such charades are common
during such stormy nights.

448
00:38:28,227 --> 00:38:30,900
And many doctors have
reported to the police.

449
00:38:31,707 --> 00:38:34,699
But we never found anything.

450
00:38:35,947 --> 00:38:37,346
What are you saying, inspector?

451
00:38:37,427 --> 00:38:39,998
That dead girl, that crying lady..

452
00:38:40,078 --> 00:38:41,696
I saw them just
now with my own eyes.

453
00:38:47,787 --> 00:38:50,301
- You come with me.
- Let's go.

454
00:38:50,627 --> 00:38:51,696
Come.

455
00:38:52,027 --> 00:38:53,096
You all stay here.

456
00:39:16,139 --> 00:39:17,139
Come with me.

457
00:40:04,307 --> 00:40:09,062
But here.. that dead girl..
That shrieking lady.. just..

458
00:40:11,707 --> 00:40:13,618
Somebody's soul is wandering.

459
00:40:16,627 --> 00:40:17,696
Come, doctor.

460
00:40:17,867 --> 00:40:18,936
It's so strange!

461
00:40:19,947 --> 00:40:22,222
When I met that girl
for the first time..

462
00:40:23,455 --> 00:40:24,867
She vanished in the graveyard.

463
00:40:25,547 --> 00:40:27,617
- What?
- That man..

464
00:40:29,227 --> 00:40:31,946
- Who?
- Nobody.

465
00:40:34,947 --> 00:40:37,381
Come. Let's go, doctor.
There's no one here.

466
00:40:46,947 --> 00:40:49,222
Bring me the tea.

467
00:40:49,627 --> 00:40:50,776
- Paper.
- Paper.

468
00:40:51,227 --> 00:40:52,455
- Is this the paper?
- No.

469
00:40:53,227 --> 00:40:54,987
The tea is fresh and
the paper is also fresh.

470
00:41:00,467 --> 00:41:02,387
- Mother has returned from the temple?
- Not yet.

471
00:41:06,867 --> 00:41:08,507
Why are you sweeping
early in the morning?

472
00:41:08,547 --> 00:41:11,220
- Let me have tea.
- Sir, along with cleaning the body..

473
00:41:11,307 --> 00:41:13,916
It is important to clean
the room in the morning too.

474
00:41:14,962 --> 00:41:15,962
Madhav, wait.

475
00:41:25,307 --> 00:41:27,104
An unknown girl in railway accident.

476
00:41:28,547 --> 00:41:29,662
Who is this unknown girl?

477
00:41:30,627 --> 00:41:33,221
The police are
investigating this accident.

478
00:41:36,251 --> 00:41:39,018
That same girl.. the same one.

479
00:41:40,027 --> 00:41:41,096
Who is she, sir?

480
00:41:41,547 --> 00:41:43,458
- How old is this paper?
- What do I know?

481
00:41:43,547 --> 00:41:46,380
- How did it come here?
- How do I know that?

482
00:41:46,467 --> 00:41:47,741
How did it come here?

483
00:41:48,366 --> 00:41:50,298
How do I know that?
It must have come somehow.

484
00:41:51,227 --> 00:41:52,296
Anything special?

485
00:42:33,833 --> 00:42:38,987
Hello! Hello!
Dr. Anand! Is it doctor Anand?

486
00:42:40,105 --> 00:42:42,946
Dr. Anand! Hello! Hello!

487
00:42:54,627 --> 00:42:57,425
- Did you send for me?
- Yes.

488
00:42:58,227 --> 00:43:00,104
Last night you got a
call from the hospital.

489
00:43:00,507 --> 00:43:02,418
And you disconnected the call. Why?

490
00:43:03,627 --> 00:43:04,987
That was a call from the hospital?

491
00:43:05,467 --> 00:43:06,536
Of course.

492
00:43:06,947 --> 00:43:09,578
- I thought it was wrong number.
- Wrong number?

493
00:43:09,658 --> 00:43:11,299
I thought it was
not some man's call.

494
00:43:12,947 --> 00:43:16,740
What do you mean?
Wrong number, some man's call.

495
00:43:17,027 --> 00:43:19,939
Do you realise, your patient
was so serious last night.

496
00:43:20,329 --> 00:43:21,363
Luckily they found
me at the clinic..

497
00:43:21,387 --> 00:43:23,147
Otherwise your
patient would have died.

498
00:43:23,227 --> 00:43:24,907
And you would have
been at court right now.

499
00:43:26,387 --> 00:43:27,456
What's the matter?

500
00:43:29,337 --> 00:43:30,337
Nothing, sir.

501
00:43:32,107 --> 00:43:33,387
I was really worried last night.

502
00:43:33,827 --> 00:43:36,366
If you remain worried then
what will happen to your patients?

503
00:43:37,387 --> 00:43:38,456
You are hiding something!

504
00:43:40,467 --> 00:43:45,780
Nothing, sir. I.. I couldn't
sleep for the past 2-3 nights.

505
00:43:49,132 --> 00:43:50,132
You couldn't sleep.

506
00:43:50,883 --> 00:43:54,382
Anand, don't make a
mockery of yourself.

507
00:43:54,947 --> 00:43:57,222
I am observing, since
the time of Seema's death..

508
00:43:57,573 --> 00:43:59,733
Neither your mind nor
your heart is in your control.

509
