01:30:49,245 --> 01:30:54,000
"It is my pain and sorrow."

1017
01:30:54,125 --> 01:30:58,641
"Why are you enduring it?"

1018
01:30:58,805 --> 01:31:06,805
"Why do you shed it from your eyes?"

1019
01:31:08,645 --> 01:31:14,800
"I have started
the fire of sorrows."

1020
01:31:15,245 --> 01:31:18,043
"Why did you start crying?"

1021
01:31:18,123 --> 01:31:24,320
"When I narrated my story to you."

1022
01:31:24,725 --> 01:31:27,239
"Why did you start crying?"

1023
01:31:44,405 --> 01:31:46,685
"I have cried a lot."

1024
01:31:46,765 --> 01:31:53,477
"But now for your sake,
I won't cry."

1025
01:31:53,885 --> 01:31:58,834
"I have lost my solace."

1026
01:31:58,925 --> 01:32:02,884
"But you won't lose yours."

1027
01:32:03,485 --> 01:32:09,481
"The doomsday
drowned in your tears."

1028
01:32:09,885 --> 01:32:12,683
"Why did you start crying?"

1029
01:32:12,765 --> 01:32:19,034
"When I narrated my story to you."

1030
01:32:19,285 --> 01:32:21,879
"Why did you start crying?"

1031
01:32:34,125 --> 01:32:37,595
"If these tears didn't stop..

1032
01:32:37,685 --> 01:32:43,362
Then I too will start crying."

1033
01:32:43,725 --> 01:32:51,725
"I will drown the moon
and the stars in my tears."

1034
01:32:53,285 --> 01:32:59,474
"The whole
creation will annihilate."

1035
01:32:59,765 --> 01:33:02,598
"Why did you start crying?"

1036
01:33:02,685 --> 01:33:08,681
"When I narrated my story to you."

1037
01:33:09,005 --> 01:33:11,678
"Why did you start crying?"

1038
01:33:11,959 --> 01:33:18,279
"My heart has been ruined."

1039
01:33:19,125 --> 01:33:24,995
"Why did you start crying?"

1040
01:34:57,165 --> 01:34:58,837
Watchman! Madhav!

1041
01:35:02,814 --> 01:35:03,814
Who came here just now?

1042
01:35:04,130 --> 01:35:05,130
Nobody, sir.

1043
01:35:05,885 --> 01:35:06,954
Did you see anybody here?

1044
01:35:07,332 --> 01:35:08,598
- No.
- What rubbish!

1045
01:35:08,846 --> 01:35:09,846
I am telling the truth.

1046
01:35:09,877 --> 01:35:11,221
We've been sitting here
for the past half an hour..

1047
01:35:11,245 --> 01:35:12,314
Nobody came.

1048
01:35:13,645 --> 01:35:15,954
- What's the matter, sir?
- Nothing.

1049
01:35:18,424 --> 01:35:21,795
- What's the matter?
- Nothing.

1050
01:35:54,165 --> 01:35:59,478
'I'm leaving. But my heart and
soul will reside here only. '

1051
01:36:00,005 --> 01:36:01,233
'With you. '

1052
01:36:03,294 --> 01:36:07,681
'I only regret that you
will again become alone. '

1053
01:37:11,385 --> 01:37:14,038
Anand! Anand, son!

1054
01:37:14,885 --> 01:37:18,116
Anand! Anand! Anand!

1055
01:37:19,045 --> 01:37:20,114
What happened, Mother?

1056
01:37:23,765 --> 01:37:24,834
What's the matter?

1057
01:37:24,914 --> 01:37:27,041
Son, a terrible thing has happened.

1058
01:37:27,485 --> 01:37:28,964
- I have bad news.
- What?

1059
01:37:29,365 --> 01:37:31,081
The train in which
daughter-in-law was travelling..

1060
01:37:31,105 --> 01:37:32,405
It has met with an accident.

1061
01:37:32,485 --> 01:37:33,679
- Accident?
- Yes.

1062
01:37:34,048 --> 01:37:36,723
See the paper.
Many people have died.

1063
01:37:36,803 --> 01:37:38,283
What time did the
accident take place?

1064
01:37:38,365 --> 01:37:39,645
At 7 o'clock in the evening.

1065
01:37:39,725 --> 01:37:40,794
Mother, she is not dead!

1066
01:37:41,005 --> 01:37:42,325
I pray for the same.

1067
01:37:42,405 --> 01:37:43,474
She can never die!

1068
01:37:44,485 --> 01:37:45,600
Only living people can die.

1069
01:37:46,205 --> 01:37:48,325
But how can the girl who
dies again and again die?

1070
01:37:48,405 --> 01:37:49,599
What are you saying?

1071
01:37:49,765 --> 01:37:51,881
You won't believe me,
Mother. I am telling the truth.

1072
01:37:52,725 --> 01:37:54,602
The train met with an
accident at 7 o'clock pm.

1073
01:37:55,605 --> 01:37:59,484
I saw her at 2 o'clock in
the night. She was here only.

1074
01:38:00,440 --> 01:38:02,037
You must have dreamt it.

1075
01:38:02,365 --> 01:38:05,038
You saw her in the dream, you
saw her before your dream too.

1076
01:38:05,765 --> 01:38:07,039
She must have survived.

1077
01:38:07,645 --> 01:38:09,601
I pray to God what you say,
that comes true.

1078
01:38:10,776 --> 01:38:11,839
Maybe she survived.

1079
01:38:12,605 --> 01:38:14,402
Son, go. Find out about her.

1080
01:38:15,066 --> 01:38:16,597
It's futile to go, Mother.

1081
01:38:17,725 --> 01:38:19,085
She is there and she is not there.

1082
01:38:19,915 --> 01:38:21,515
She will be found
and she won't be found.

1083
01:38:21,725 --> 01:38:23,477
I can't understand your riddle.

1084
01:38:24,297 --> 01:38:27,289
Have mercy on me.
Find my daughter-in-law.

1085
01:38:28,457 --> 01:38:32,166
Sir, let's go.
We should go and check out

1086
01:38:32,857 --> 01:38:35,246
Son, go. Go.

1087
01:39:00,217 --> 01:39:03,289
Let's go, sir. Now what is here now?

1088
01:39:06,804 --> 01:39:11,971
Doctor, Anand's plight is such
that I can't endure to see it.

1089
01:39:12,051 --> 01:39:14,247
Yes. I understand.

1090
01:39:14,937 --> 01:39:19,169
After Seema, Sandhya's
death came as a shock to him.

1091
01:39:19,464 --> 01:39:21,767
I suggest you to take
him to Shimla immediately.

1092
01:39:21,977 --> 01:39:23,330
My mansion is unoccupied there.

1093
01:39:23,410 --> 01:39:25,215
And you won't have trouble too.

1094
01:39:25,295 --> 01:39:27,248
If you want, you can
take Lata with you.

1095
01:40:02,695 --> 01:40:06,366
Is somebody there?
Is somebody inside?

1096
01:40:06,977 --> 01:40:08,046
Nobody is here.

1097
01:40:08,457 --> 01:40:09,526
Some servant must be here.

1098
01:40:09,777 --> 01:40:12,894
Nobody is there.
This place is so terrifying, ma'am.

1099
01:40:12,974 --> 01:40:14,416
You are scared of everyplace.

1100
01:40:14,496 --> 01:40:15,606
What is there to fear?

1101
01:40:15,686 --> 01:40:17,090
There is nothing to fear, ma'am.

1102
01:40:20,817 --> 01:40:21,886
Did you hear that?

1103
01:40:23,737 --> 01:40:25,375
There is no sound.

1104
01:40:26,457 --> 01:40:28,448
It seems to be an abode of ghosts.

1105
01:40:28,528 --> 01:40:30,886
What rubbish! No ghosts dwell here.

1106
01:40:30,966 --> 01:40:32,291
Ghosts are not trustworthy.

1107
01:40:32,371 --> 01:40:35,409
They don't need ticket,
or train or plane.

1108
01:40:35,489 --> 01:40:37,225
And they don't even need
warm clothes for winter.

1109
01:40:37,249 --> 01:40:39,049
Maybe they have arrived before us.

1110
01:40:39,129 --> 01:40:40,129
Shut up! Let's go in!

1111
01:40:40,163 --> 01:40:41,326
- Son, come.
- Let's go.

1112
01:40:41,406 --> 01:40:42,742
Let all troubles vanish.

1113
01:40:43,541 --> 01:40:47,093
Let all troubles vanish.

1114
01:40:48,897 --> 01:40:50,615
Sher Singh! Sher Singh!

1115
01:40:50,695 --> 01:40:53,689
Ma'am, listen to me.
Nobody is seen here.

1116
01:40:53,769 --> 01:40:56,179
If we stayed in a hotel, at
least we will see somebody.

1117
01:40:56,259 --> 01:40:57,566
Please come.

1118
01:41:04,571 --> 01:41:06,847
They too are going inside.

1119
01:41:07,377 --> 01:41:10,016
Oh, God! Somebody is coming.

1120
01:41:10,617 --> 01:41:11,891
I can't see it.

1121
01:41:13,217 --> 01:41:15,367
- Greetings.
- Ghost.

1122
01:41:16,177 --> 01:41:17,037
Who are you?

1123
01:41:17,117 --> 01:41:19,845
I am Sher Singh. The
caretaker of this place.

1124
01:41:19,937 --> 01:41:20,805
The caretaker of this place?

1125
01:41:20,885 --> 01:41:22,313
It means you have
been working here..

1126
01:41:22,337 --> 01:41:23,462
Since the time
this mansion was built?

1127
01:41:23,486 --> 01:41:24,870
I was even born here.

1128
01:41:24,950 --> 01:41:28,931
You were born here! Tell me,
is there any ghost here?

1129
01:41:29,177 --> 01:41:32,537
Ghost? Only ghosts dwell here.

1130
01:41:32,617 --> 01:41:33,845
There are all kinds of ghosts.

1131
01:41:34,177 --> 01:41:36,168
- Do you see that tree?
- Yes.

1132
01:41:36,248 --> 01:41:37,525
A spirit dwells there.

1133
01:41:37,777 --> 01:41:39,593
If you go a bit further,
you will find a witch.

1134
01:41:39,617 --> 01:41:42,177
- Witch!
- Yes. She sings at 12 o'clock at night.

1135
01:41:42,257 --> 01:41:43,033
She sings at 12 o'clock at night.

1136
01:41:43,113 --> 01:41:45,233
- And at the backyard of this mansion..
- I don't care who is there.

1137
01:41:45,257 --> 01:41:46,666
But I hope nobody is
inside the mansion.

1138
01:41:46,690 --> 01:41:49,490
- Inside the mansion..
- Sher Singh! Sher Singh!

1139
01:41:49,570 --> 01:41:52,848
- Coming! I will tell you later.
- Fine.

1140
01:41:53,512 --> 01:41:56,415
He is Sher as well as Singh (lion ).
What's the time now?

1141
01:41:56,667 --> 01:41:58,369
She sings at 12 O'clock at night.

1142
01:42:16,457 --> 01:42:20,190
- Who are you?
- Who are you?

1143
01:42:20,270 --> 01:42:21,985
- Who are you?
- Who are you?

1144
01:42:22,065 --> 01:42:23,217
Who are you?

1145
01:42:23,297 --> 01:42:25,470
Forget that! Tell me,
what is your name?

1146
01:42:25,822 --> 01:42:28,047
My name! My name is Sher Singh!

1147
01:42:30,520 --> 01:42:32,957
- What is your name?
- My name is Billi ( cat ) Singh.

1148
01:42:33,037 --> 01:42:35,922
- Billi Singh?
- Yes. - What is that?

1149
01:42:36,002 --> 01:42:39,537
Billi Singh. Here I am.
This is Madhav.

1150
01:42:39,617 --> 01:42:43,451
Oh, God! Madhav, you scared me.

1151
01:42:44,727 --> 01:42:46,608
Tell me. What's the time?

1152
01:42:46,688 --> 01:42:48,783
- Time?
- Yes. - Must be 11 o'clock.

1153
01:42:48,863 --> 01:42:50,046
- 11 o'clock?
- Yes.

1154
01:42:50,126 --> 01:42:52,850
- The clock will strike 12 after an hour.
- Yes, of course..

1155
01:42:52,930 --> 01:42:54,451
- Tell me.
- Yes.

1156
01:42:54,817 --> 01:42:57,536
- At what time does the ghost come out?
- Ghost? -Yes.

1157
01:42:57,617 --> 01:43:00,256
Madhav, do ghosts
have any fixed time?

1158
01:43:00,336 --> 01:43:01,696
They will come whenever they want.

1159
01:43:01,759 --> 01:43:03,928
I have heard that
they come at 12 o'clock.

1160
01:43:04,081 --> 01:43:05,291
- 12 o'clock?
- Yes.

1161
01:43:05,515 --> 01:43:07,414
How will I pass this night?

1162
01:43:07,494 --> 01:43:10,256
Madhav, this is a hilly region.

1163
01:43:10,441 --> 01:43:11,731
Nights here are cold.

1164
01:43:11,817 --> 01:43:12,886
- Is that so?
- Yes.

1165
01:43:13,057 --> 01:43:14,743
What time do they sing?

1166
01:43:14,823 --> 01:43:16,872
Between 1 and 3.

1167
01:43:16,952 --> 01:43:18,854
- Between 1 and 3?
- Yes.

1168
01:43:19,097 --> 01:43:23,534
- Do they sing all kinds of songs?
- Yes.

1169
01:43:23,614 --> 01:43:25,369
Nowadays they even sing movie songs.

1170
01:43:25,449 --> 01:43:27,613
- They even sing movie songs?
- Yes.

1171
01:43:46,417 --> 01:43:48,612
- Who is she?
- Madhumati.

1172
01:43:48,937 --> 01:43:50,223
- Madhumati?
- Yes.

1173
01:43:50,303 --> 01:43:52,248
- Padmavati's sister?
- No.

1174
01:43:52,457 --> 01:43:55,767
- Sher Singh, you go inside.
- Sher Singh!

1175
01:43:55,847 --> 01:43:58,730
You go inside! And
where should I go?

1176
01:44:52,337 --> 01:44:53,406
Come.

1177
01:44:57,937 --> 01:44:59,609
Son, look who has come.

1178
01:45:08,602 --> 01:45:09,806
Who are you?

1179
01:45:10,577 --> 01:45:12,169
It's good that you have come.

1180
01:45:13,537 --> 01:45:15,607
Now you can't leave this place.

1181
01:45:24,177 --> 01:45:27,613
Mother, who was he?

1182
01:45:28,617 --> 01:45:32,007
Madhav says that he is a
great saint of this place.

1183
01:45:32,610 --> 01:45:34,614
But why did he leave like this?

1184
01:45:36,057 --> 01:45:37,888
I feel very strange.

1185
01:45:43,605 --> 01:45:45,534
- What are you writing?
- Nothing! Nothing!

1186
01:45:45,614 --> 01:45:47,334
If it's nothing, then
why are you hiding it?

1187
01:45:47,777 --> 01:45:49,369
I was writing a poem.

1188
01:45:49,617 --> 01:45:52,973
A poem? The way I write lyrics.

1189
01:45:53,737 --> 01:45:56,046
Lyrics, what is that?

1190
01:45:56,126 --> 01:45:59,249
It is what it is.
But what is a poem?

1191
01:46:00,137 --> 01:46:02,177
Poem is what a poet writes.

1192
01:46:02,257 --> 01:46:03,975
Lyric is what a
talented person writes.

1193
01:46:05,017 --> 01:46:06,168
What is that?

1194
01:46:06,248 --> 01:46:10,012
It is what it is.
But what is this poet?

1195
01:46:10,737 --> 01:46:14,920
Poet! The person who writes poems.

1196
01:46:15,000 --> 01:46:17,173
Talented person is the
one who writes lyrics.

1197
01:46:17,744 --> 01:46:19,176
What is that?

1198
01:46:19,345 --> 01:46:22,767
That is what it is.
But what is this poem?

1199
01:46:23,377 --> 01:46:25,049
- What is poem?
- Yes.

1200
01:46:25,318 --> 01:46:26,526
- Shall I tell you?
- Yes.

1201
01:46:29,444 --> 01:46:30,890
- Tell me.
- She has come.

1202
01:46:30,970 --> 01:46:32,030
- She has come?
- Yes.

1203
01:46:32,110 --> 01:46:35,806
- Tell me.
- The way a cuckoo sings in a garden.

1204
01:46:36,701 --> 01:46:38,416
Lyric goes something like this.

1205
01:46:38,496 --> 01:46:40,767
The way a crow sings on a tree.

1206
01:46:41,399 --> 01:46:42,799
- Shall I explain it to you?
- What?

1207
01:46:42,825 --> 01:46:44,513
- Shall I explain it to you?
- No, I have understood.

1208
01:46:44,537 --> 01:46:45,606
Then give me a cigarette.

1209
01:46:58,415 --> 01:46:59,815
You don't want to come for skating?

1210
01:47:00,298 --> 01:47:01,730
Everybody is waiting downstairs.

1211
01:47:02,217 --> 01:47:03,809
You guys go. I will be there soon.

1212
01:47:04,481 --> 01:47:06,414
- Please.
- Okay.

1213
01:47:43,777 --> 01:47:46,735
- Were you looking out for me?
- Yes.

1214
01:47:47,057 --> 01:47:48,617
Are you searching
for somebody else too?

1215
01:47:49,057 --> 01:47:50,615
Life itself is a search.

1216
01:47:50,891 --> 01:47:53,093
And you have got
lost in that search.

1217
01:47:54,377 --> 01:47:58,290
I know I have lost my way.
I admit that I am searching.

1218
01:47:59,213 --> 01:48:00,709
But I don't know what
I am searching for..

1219
01:48:00,733 --> 01:48:02,530
And for what I
am wandering around.

1220
01:48:02,653 --> 01:48:04,644
- You will find out.
- When?

1221
01:48:04,933 --> 01:48:07,288
- When the time is right.
- When the time is right?

1222
01:48:07,653 --> 01:48:11,646
Yes. And at that time you'll
come to meet me on your own.

1223
01:48:54,253 --> 01:48:58,371
"The lightening of the sly eyes."

1224
01:48:58,973 --> 01:49:03,633
"Strike it in my heart."

1225
01:49:03,713 --> 01:49:07,692
"Don't worry about me."

1226
01:49:08,320 --> 01:49:12,843
"You just keep smiling."

1227
01:49:12,923 --> 01:49:17,444
"The lightening of the sly eyes."

1228
01:49:35,533 --> 01:49:39,492
"The desires have aroused."

1229
01:49:40,093 --> 01:49:43,881
"Glimmering in the heart."

1230
01:49:44,653 --> 01:49:48,692
"On the path of faithfulness."

1231
01:49:49,158 --> 01:49:53,006
"I have started
walking along with you."

1232
01:49:53,813 --> 01:49:57,647
"If you want, you
can make me laugh."

1233
01:49:58,413 --> 01:50:03,009
"If you want, you can make me cry."

1234
01:50:03,089 --> 01:50:07,092
"The lightening of the sly eyes."

1235
01:50:07,653 --> 01:50:12,249
"Strike it in my heart."

1236
01:50:12,333 --> 01:50:16,963
"The lightening of the sly eyes."

1237
01:50:44,413 --> 01:50:48,201
"The destination of
love is far away."

1238
01:50:48,893 --> 01:50:52,772
"It is very far away."

1239
01:50:53,533 --> 01:50:57,526
"Come and hold my hands."

1240
01:50:58,093 --> 01:51:01,972
"The soul is not far away."

1241
01:51:02,773 --> 01:51:07,051
"Leaving your world."

1242
01:51:07,413 --> 01:51:11,929
"Enter my world."

1243
01:51:12,053 --> 01:51:16,092
"The lightening of the sly eyes."

1244
01:51:16,653 --> 01:51:21,204
"Strike it in my heart."

1245
01:51:21,293 --> 01:51:25,889
"The lightening of the sly eyes."

1246
01:52:40,533 --> 01:52:41,648
What's the matter, Anand?

1247
01:52:47,693 --> 01:52:49,206
What's the matter, Anand?

1248
01:52:49,893 --> 01:52:51,087
I saw her again.

1249
01:52:52,018 --> 01:52:53,964
Whom? Whom, Anand?

1250
01:52:57,794 --> 01:52:58,962
Nobody.

1251
01:53:07,093 --> 01:53:10,927
'Daddy, I think it is
deeply affecting his mind. '

1252
01:53:11,693 --> 01:53:13,763
'He had seen somebody. '

1253
01:53:14,533 --> 01:53:16,410
'But when I asked him, he refused. '

1254
01:53:17,253 --> 01:53:18,925
'Now it could prove
even more dangerous.'

1255
01:53:44,213 --> 01:53:46,329
Your time has arrived.

1256
01:53:47,311 --> 01:53:49,522
Good that you have come.

1257
01:53:59,213 --> 01:54:00,282
March ahead.

1258
01:54:04,081 --> 01:54:06,208
This is the end of your journey.

1259
01:54:16,118 --> 01:54:18,647
- Do you see anything?
- Nothing.

1260
01:54:18,733 --> 01:54:20,963
You won't see
anything with these eyes.

1261
01:54:22,493 --> 01:54:26,532
Soul is craving for
the soul. Not your body.

1262
01:54:27,093 --> 01:54:31,291
If you want to see her, then
let go of your physical body.

1263
01:54:32,413 --> 01:54:35,166
The soul that has been
